The paper deals with the computational complexity of approximating the Tutte polynomial of a planar graph, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The fact that the problem specifically concerns planar graphs suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves some results related to graph coloring, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
